entry.title: Ukraine Scrambles to Restore Power After Russian Strikes
entry.content: Authorities worked to bring back electricity supplies in several cities including Kyiv, a day after a Russian missile barrage damaged critical infrastructure across the country.

entry.title: As Japan Runs Short of Farmworkers, Bureaucrats Get Sent Into the Fields
entry.content: Across Japan, where the population has been shrinking for over a decade and nearly a third of people are at least 65 years old, the hunt for manual labor has reached city hall.
